optimized.result:
**Professional Bio: Rudy**

Rudy is an accomplished computer science student in the final year of a rigorous program at the University of Toronto, where he maintains an impressive CGPA of 3.91 out of 4.00. Specializing in artificial intelligence, mathematics, and statistics, Rudy is deeply committed to the intersection of AI and software engineering, focusing on developing scalable systems that deliver tangible value to users.

Currently, Rudy is honing his skills as a Software Engineering Intern at Intact Financial Corporation. His work involves engineering dependency visualization systems using Clojure/Angular, automating OpenShift cluster management, and optimizing release cycles. In addition to his internship, Rudy is actively building and contributing to the AI/ML ecosystem as an entrepreneur with Shopify Builder Sundays.

Rudy's academic and professional journey is marked by significant achievements. He has published research on particle swarm optimization for feature selection in classification models and has previously worked on logical query answering over knowledge graphs using large language models (LLMs) at the Computational Social Sciences Lab under Professor Ashton Anderson. His efforts in developing ontology-guided entity extraction systems at the Urban Data Center and working on autocolorization of black and white images at UTMIST underscore his passion for innovation.

Rudy has also led impactful projects, such as reducing dashboard cloning times by 93.6% for UNICEF across over 100 offices and co-founding an ed-tech startup as part of the UofT Hatchery NEST program. His technical expertise extends to full-stack development, having built platforms for Hack the 6ix and automated testing processes during his tenure at EnrichAI.

Outside of his technical endeavors, Rudy is an avid rock climber and hip-hop enthusiast, often sharing insights into his life as a university student through YouTube videos. His diverse interests and dedication to innovation make him a dynamic contributor to the fields of AI and software engineering.

For more about Rudy's projects and to connect, visit his portfolio at [Rudy's Portfolio](https://whyismynamerudy-techv3-ai-optimized.vercel.app/).

# hi, i'm rudy.

## welcome to mylittle corner of the world wide web

-> compsci, math, and stats student @ uoft-> buildingimpactful,scalable, andsecuresoftware-> passionate about machine learning, artificial intelligence, and innovation

### about.

hello world🫡, i'm rudy. i'm pursuing knowledge at the intersection of ai and software engineering, with a focus on building systems that scale and bring value to users.

outside of tech, i'm into rock climbing, hip-hop, and working out. you'll often find me listening to the latesthip-hopsongs or filming ayoutubevideo about my life as a university student.

now:

engineering dependency visualization systems in clojure/angular, automating openshift cluster management, and streamlining release cycles atintact financial corporationas a software engineering intern.

building and contributing to the ai/ml ecosystem as an entrepreneur atshopify builder sundays.

entering my final year at uoft (cgpa: 3.91/4.00), studying computer science with a focus in ai, mathematics, and statistics.

previously:

researched logical query answering over knowledge graphs using llms atthe computational social sciences labunder prof. ashton anderson.

developed ontology-guided entity extraction systems using llms at theurban data center.

worked on autocolorization of black and white images atutmist, implementing and expanding on “colorful image colorization” by richard zhang et al.

led development of an open-source dashboard cloning system atunicefthat reduced clone times by 93.6% across 100+ offices.

co-founded and served as cto of an ed-tech startup in theuoft hatcherynest program.

built the website and developer platform as a full stack developer athack the 6ix.

automated testing processes as a swe intern atenrichai.

publishedresearchon particle swarm optimization for feature selection in classification models.

Rudy is a dynamic computer science student at the University of Toronto, where he is completing his final year with an impressive CGPA of 3.91/4.00. His academic focus lies at the intersection of artificial intelligence, mathematics, and statistics, reflecting his passion for machine learning, artificial intelligence, and innovative software engineering.

Currently, Rudy is gaining hands-on experience as a Software Engineering Intern at Intact Financial Corporation. In this role, he is involved in engineering dependency visualization systems using Clojure/Angular, automating OpenShift cluster management, and streamlining release cycles. Additionally, Rudy is expanding his entrepreneurial skills by contributing to the AI/ML ecosystem through Shopify's Builder Sundays.

Rudy's previous experiences include researching logical query answering over knowledge graphs using large language models at the Computational Social Sciences Lab under Professor Ashton Anderson. He also developed ontology-guided entity extraction systems at the Urban Data Center and worked on auto-colorization of black and white images at UTMIST, leveraging the "Colorful Image Colorization" technique by Richard Zhang et al.

As a co-founder and former CTO of an ed-tech startup in the UofT HatcheryNest program, Rudy honed his leadership and technical skills. He has also led the development of an open-source dashboard cloning system for UNICEF, significantly reducing clone times across multiple offices.

Rudy's technical toolkit includes a range of languages, frameworks, and databases. He has developed several notable projects, such as "Pitch Please," an AI-powered pitch feedback system, and "UnsearchableTO," which uses AI to make Toronto searchable by over half a million objects.

Outside of his technical pursuits, Rudy enjoys rock climbing, hip-hop, and working out. He often creates YouTube content about his experiences as a university student. Rudy welcomes connections via email or LinkedIn, where he is eager to engage with like-minded individuals passionate about technology and innovation.
